meanings.definition: To push out or force out
meanings.sent1: She was outpushing the heavy door to open it.
meanings.sent2: The workers were outpushing the carts filled with boxes.
meanings.sent3: The robot kept outpushing the buttons on the control panel by mistake.
meanings.sent4: The wind was outpushing the clouds across the sky.
meanings.sent5: The child was outpushing the swing higher and higher.

meanings.definition: The act of pushing out or forcing out
meanings.sent1: The outpushing of air from the balloon made it fly away.
meanings.sent2: The outpushing of water from the hose was strong and steady.
meanings.sent3: The outpushing of toys from the box surprised the children.
meanings.sent4: The outpushing of leaves from the tree created a colorful carpet on the ground.
meanings.sent5: The outpushing of steam from the kettle signaled that the water was boiling.
